                  </hi>, <hi rend="italic">assistant to Mr. Aldhouse, pawnbroker.</hi> On the 27th of May, Pizeley pledged this shawl and some silk—he told me he pledged it for Gates.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440610-name-910" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-910" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-910" type="surname" value="BEVAN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440610-name-910" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY BEVAN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable, F</hi> 3.) On this Thursday, I took Pizeley into custody at Hammersmith—he said he was employed by Gates to pledge the things for 4<hi rend="italic">s</hi>., and he took the ticket, and likewise the money to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Pizeley's Defence.</hi> Between three and four o'clock on Monday afternoon, I was in the skittle-ground with my own companion; Gates came and asked me to pawn the things for him; he said they were his sister's; I pawned them, and gave the ticket and money to him.</p>
